# References & Standards

This document lists all standards, specifications, and libraries that informed the design and implementation of Cert-V2X.

---

## IEEE Standards

**IEEE 1609.2-2016** — *IEEE Standard for Wireless Access in Vehicular Environments — Security Services for Applications and Management Messages*
- Defines the V2X certificate format, COER-encoded ASN.1 data structures, PSID-based application permissions, Authorization Ticket structure, and the enrollment/authorization PKI flows.
- Amendment: **IEEE 1609.2a-2017** — updated cryptographic algorithm support (ecdsaNistP256, ecdsaBrainpoolP256r1)
- https://standards.ieee.org/ieee/1609.2/6085/

---

## ETSI Standards

**ETSI TS 103 097 V1.3.1** — *Intelligent Transport Systems (ITS); Security; Security header and certificate formats*
- EU equivalent of IEEE 1609.2 for ITS PKI. Defines `EtsiTs103097Certificate`, `EtsiTs103097Data`, and secure message profiles (CAM, DENM).
- https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/103000_103099/103097/01.03.01_60/ts_103097v010301p.pdf

**ETSI TS 102 941 V1.3.1** — *Intelligent Transport Systems (ITS); Security; Trust and Privacy Management*
- Defines the ITS PKI message flows: Enrolment Request/Response, Authorization Request/Response, Authorization Validation, CRL/CTL generation.
- https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/102900_102999/102941/01.03.01_60/ts_102941v010301p.pdf

